# Reflection

## What I Learned

Exploratory testing encourages curiosity and critical thinking. By interacting with the application naturally, I discovered usability concerns and workflow issues that might not be identified through predefined test cases alone.

---

## What I'd Do Differently

For a production system, I would perform exploratory testing across multiple browsers, devices, and user roles. I would also combine exploratory testing with session-based testing to ensure comprehensive coverage while maintaining clear documentation of findings.

